I made another Luxord fic. This is a sequel to "Demyx gets a Royal Rainbow and Luxord gets a paper-cut". Enjoy! (Reviews are much appreciated!) Title: The Graceful Assassin Fandom: Kingdom Hearts 2 Summary: Luxord and Axel discover Marluxia Rating: G

The Graceful Assassin

Axel clapped his hands encouragingly. "Very impressive, Luxord. Very impressive."

Razor-sharp cards erupted from Luxord's hands and punctured his gambler minions with great force, sometimes severing a limb. Lassoing a dusk with a dusk with a string of cards, he flung it across the training room effortlessly. He tossed explosive dice at the surrounding nobodies, and he grinned. He too was impressed with his new powers.

Luxord snapped his fingers, and the field of nobodies vanished instantly. He walked up the stairs to greet Axel.

He ran his pale hand through his flaming red hair casually, and he bent down to scratch his knee. "You seen Demyx?"

"A couple hours ago I heard him humming something about a sanctuary. Hey Axel, do you play poker?" Luxord pulled a battered deck of cards out of his pocket and waved them around enticingly.

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

"Oh. What happened here?" Axel said, pointing at the chipped paint on the white table. Being a very keen observer, he was sure to notice every detail of his surroundings. It was raining, as usual, and Axel's hair was drenched in the empty precipitation of the World That Never Was. Axel glanced at Luxord, who was busy dealing.

"Demyx," he growled without looking up. Once done dealing, he stood up and stretched. His eyes widened abruptly in disbelief. "Now that's an odd sight," for over the ledge of Havoc's Divide, there was a huge white swarm of dusks running, dashing, jumping, and floating towards Memory's Skyscraper. "Let's go check it out."

Stepping into a portal to darkness summoned by Axel, Luxord and Axel wondered what was going on. I've been here for a week, and there's already some excitement. What a treat.

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

"Wow, she's kind of hot." Axel and Luxord perched on top of Memory's Skyscraper, watching with interest as the stranger with long, rosy pink hair fought the surrounding cloud of dusks. With her small pocket knife she gracefully wove in and out of the curious dusks. They watched her with interest as she attempted to harm them with her pitiful excuse for a weapon.

"Um, Axel, that's a guy," Luxord said, followed by an awkward silence. "Axel, are you-"

"No, I'm not!" Axel blushed furiously. "Do you think we should go down and help her - uh, him?"

"Why bother going down?" Luxord summoned a pillar of cards, shielding the stranger from the lower nobodies, who weren't even attacking. He snapped his fingers, and the cards became a platform beneath the stranger's feet. The stranger looked disoriented, but kept his balance well as the platform took him to the peak of Memory's Skyscraper. He stepped off onto the roof, where Luxord and Axel were standing, and held his knife in front of him protectively. Droplets of water fell from his flowery hair onto the knife, making a soft clink. A look of fearful confidence showed clearly on his taut countenance.

Luxord stared at Axel. "Do you think he's a no-"

"Yep."

"Take him to Superior?"

"Yep."

Luxord constricted the struggling stranger with a rope of cards as Axel opened a portal to darkness. Luxord shoved the stranger inside, and the three nobodies were wisked away to the Altar of Naught.

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

"Luxord, I am afraid you must give Marluxia the Orientation. Axel is barely what you could call 'capable.' I would do it myself, but I have other, more important matters to attend to. Now go. Teach Marluxia, the Graceful Assassin, everything.

I made a new Luxord fic. This is a sequel to "Enter Luxord", if you read it. Title: Demyx Gets a Royal Rainbow and Luxord Gets a Paper-cut Fandom: Kingdom Hearts 2 Rating: G Summary: Luxord develops his odd method of fighting Disclaimers: I DON'T OWN KINGDOM HEARTS 2 (but I own a copy of the game)
Demyx Gets a Royal Rainbow and Luxord Gets a Paper-cut
Luxord walked down the hall to his room in his new coat and boots. The hollow sound of his solemn footsteps bounced off of the blindeningly white walls and surrounded him. Passing a few more doors, he came to his:
Luxord #10 The Gambler of Fate
Placing his gloved hand on the doorknob, he twisted and pushed. Nice setup, he thought as he entered his new living quarters. A lot better than the streets. He flopped onto his twin-sized bed and stared at the ceiling. Too much had happened in the past few hours. Superior had taught him what he was - a nobody: one of the side-effects of the loss of a hearts. He was accepted by neither light nor dark, and he teetered on the brink of existence. He was an outcast, along with all the other members of the Orginazation. They were all nobodies. It was brutal really, the way Superior taught him how the nobodies came into existence (or nonexistence as the case may be). Using a live human, he had a neoshadow steal her heart, thus resulting in another heartless, and a nobody. Luxord thought the mission of collecting hearts was questionably harsh, but he would give anything to be whole again. He hated the knowledge and feeling of being empty - of being nothing. On the other hand, he felt he fit in with the Orginazation. He finally felt he was home. Luxord snapped his fingers and a portal to the realm of darkness appeared. He looked down at his fingers with a more-than-satisfactory admiration. Nifty. ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ Tap. Tap. Tap. Tap. The rhythmic thumping of Demyx's fingers on wood permeated the tense silence of Havoc's Divide. The usually still air seemed agitated and annoyed. The white paint on the table had began to peel where Demyx's calusses collided with the gambling surface. Taptaptap. Taptaptaptap. "Demyx!" Luxord growled. He glared at his opponent. "You've been sitting there for the last half-hour tapping your fingers on this cheap table! The cards you have are the cards you have! Now, are you going to bet, or are you going to fold!" Luxord hated playing poker, or any card game for that matter, with Demyx. He would've rather played with Saix, or Axel, but they were both out, doing who-knows-what. It's like he's trying to make me want to strangle him, Luxord thought. He just sits there, tapping his fingers and humming his stupid tune. Demyx pushed in 10 munnys to the middle of the table. Luxord looked at his cards. He had a straight. Considering he options, he thought about what kind of hand Demyx had. Well, Demyx didn't seem like the king of person to play poker. He knew Demyx would probably never bet on anything good. Nonetheless, Luxord had to consider the fact that Demyx might get lucky and win, so he didn't raise too much. "I see your 10, and I raise you 5." Luxord triamphuntly threw in 15 munnys, followed by Demyx, who added 5 more munnys to the pot. Luxord smirked and spread his cards on the table. He arched his eyebrows and looked at Demyx expectantly. Demyx reluctantly laid down his hand: 2,4, 5, 9, and an Ace. "They're all the same color. I have a Royal Rainbow," he said confidently. "I win." He began to sweep the munnys to his side. I guess Demyx just isn't meant for gambling. "Sorry Demyx, but I win. You have nothing." Demyx looked hurt. When Luxord was done gathering his winnings, Demyx stepped out of his chair and stretched. "I'm not sure if I'm gonna play cards with you again, Lux. I think my munny is just.... attracted to you," he said. He stepped through the door to Proof of Existence. Luxord laughed. He was finally fitting in somewhere. He finally knew people. He had left his life of living on the streets, barely clinging onto existence. Now, he had let go of existence. Now he was nothing. Maybe that's all he was meant to be. He snapped his fingers and the table and chairs vanished, just as his old life had, right before his eyes. ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ "Hey, Xigbar, you play poker?" Luxord was in the training room training against a few of his gambler nobodies. Sweat soaked his brow as he dodged back and forth between the swift streams of cards spewing from his underlings. The dim light of the room provided a good training environment, and allowed the Gambler of Fate to home in on his senses. "Gotta love it!" Xigbar was of course at the shooting range. All the targets had been demolished, and they looked as if they had been chewed into. "Where'd you get that gun?" Luxord asked enviously while he threw punches at the gamblers. He eyed Xigbar as he applied pressure tot he trigger of his unique weapon. A couple of bright red lasers shot out of the gun and hit the target right on the dot. "Crossbow, actually. I won it playing poker, matter o' fact. I was playin' with some hooded guy I met in Twilight Town," Xigbar replied indignantly as he fired a couple more rounds. "I am sorry. The shooting range is - am sorry - am sorry - a - a - am - s - so - s - sor - am - sorry - a -" the shooting range croaked, and then it exploded into tiny chunks of metal and wire. "Fine! Be that way!" Xigbar scowled, and stormed up the stairs and out of the room. Luxord chuckled a little as his foot came in contact with a gambler's face. Xigbar is...... weird. Luxord felt a sharp stinging pain in his shoulder and looked to his left. There was a paper-cut left by one of the gamblers' cards. That gave him and idea....

I'm applying for Luxord in an RP, and I thought maybe you would like to read it. Feedback is welcome! :) Application: LJ Username: Character You Are Applying For: Luxord Character Interpretation (basically...your take on the character and what makes them tick--if you are applying for an Org member, we want some background on who their Somebody may have been...): Somebody: As all nobodies were, Luxord was once somebody. Dulor was born into an extremely poor family in Hollow Bastion. His father drank away all their money, while his mother was turned into a heartless when he was only six. His five brothers were all older than him, and worked hard to keep the family going. Dulor was witty, and sometimes a smartaleck. One day, Dulor's pitiful house, that was more of a shack, caught fire and was turned to ashes. Only Dulor survived. Dulor, age 14, was forced to live on the streets, surviving on scraps of food, and charity from the more fortunate. 3 years after the incident, he discovered he had a nack for gambling. He was a very strategical thinker, and when it came to poker, he was the best. Playing poker on the streets with a deck of cards given to him by his mother, Nareel, he was able to scavenge a living. However, Dulor's "winning streak" came to an end when his heart was taken by a NeoShadow. Nobody: Looking around bewildered, Dulor found himself in the World that Never Was. Confused and disoriented, he found a colossal castle. Hobbling up the steps, he collapsed at the entrance. Xemnas found him, and he was sure. This nobdoy would be Luxord, #10 in Organization XIII. Xemnas recognized his strategically advanced mind and knew that Luxord would bring Xemnas one step closer to obtaining his goal: Kingdom Hearts. Luxord learned that his mother, Nareel, had in fact become a nobody, Larxene. Luxord was hopeful of finding her, but his hopes vanished just as Nareel had. Larxene had been killed by the keyblade weilder, Sora. Luxord didn't care who this Sora was - Sora would pay for the death of Larxene. This hate for Sora burned within him, and Luxord devised a new way of fighting. By using his inhuman gambling skills, he was able to use cards and dice to harm his foes. Luxord loved his new home. He loved always having something to do, some hearts to take. It was so much better than his past life on the streets. Him and Demyx became close friends. Usually, Luxord preffered to be alone, but he always welcomed the company of the slightly annoying Demyx. A Sample of "In-Character" Writing (at least 2-3 paragraphs): Tap. Tap. Tap. Tap. The rhythmic thumping of Demyx's fingers on wood permeated the tense silence of Havoc's Divide. The usually still air seemed agitated and annoyed. The white paint on the table had began to peel where Demyx's calusses collided with the gambling surface. Taptaptap. Taptaptaptap. "Demyx!" Luxord growled. He glared at his opponent. "You've been sitting there for the last half-hour tapping your fingers on this cheap table! The cards you have are the cards you have! Now, are you going to bet, or are you going to fold!" Luxord hated playing poker, or any card game for that matter, with Demyx. He much preffered playing with Saix, or Axel, but they were both out, doing who-knows-what. It's like he's trying to make me want to strangle him, Luxord thought. He just sits there, tapping his fingers and humming his stupid tune. Demyx pushed in 10 munnys to the middle of the table. Luxord looked at his cards. He had a straight. He knew Demyx too well. He knew Demyx never bet on anything good. Nonetheless, Luxord had to consider the fact that Demyx might get lucky and win, so he didn't raise too much. "I see your 10, and I raise you 5." Luxord triamphuntly threw in 15 munnys, followed by Demyx, who added 5 more munnys to the pot. Luxord smirked and spread his cards on the table. He arched his eyebrows and looked at Demyx expectantly. Demyx reluctantly laid down his hand: 2,4, 5, 9, and an Ace. "They're all the same color," he said confidently. "I win." He began to sweep the munnys to his side. I guess Demyx just isn't meant for gambling. "Sorry Demyx, but I win. You have nothing." Demyx looked hurt. When Luxord was done gathering his winnings, Demyx stepped out of his chair. "I remember when I would play with Larxene. She was a lot like you, Lux. See you around," he said. He stepped through the door to Proof of Existence. Luxord grunted. You're lucky Demyx. I never got to play with Nareel, or Larxene. He got up out of his chair and looked up towards the growing Kingdom Hearts. "SORA!!!!!" He snapped his fingers and the table and chairs vanished, just like everything good in his life from long ago. A Vague Idea of Where you would like to Take your Character/What you Want out of this RP: In Port Royal, the first time I saw Luxord, I thought immediately, Who is this guy? He's awesome! I was totally looking forward to see Luxord have an active role in the game, and was utterly disappointed when he appeared in, what, two or three cutscenes? I thought he was wrongly underdeveloped, for he was such an awesome guy. To be able to make him the nobody he never was is basically what I want to do. I want to make it feel like he actually was in the game, that he wasn't just some nobody (no pun intended). I'm not exactly sure where I'm going to take him, but I have some ideas. I just want to make sure he doesn't end up nowhere. Please consider,
